Data wrangling with dplyr

Todays practical is all about how to manipulate data using dplyr

Were going to be working through a lot of problems. If you struggle with them, then dont worry. You can also come back to these problems are your confidence builds. With some practise youll start to find the problems easier.

To access the problems, Ive made an RMarkdown document for you to work through. Youll just been filling in the code chunks to complete the problems. All the problems have example output. Take a look at the example output to help you work through the problem. Try things out, see what happens, and eventually youll get it right!

Good luck!
